multiLocaleSummary.en_US:
Starting my career as a sales at Amazon Web Services and Google, followed by Venture Capital, I excel at building and scaling high-growth B2B companies by architecting intelligent, repeatable Go-To-Market engines.

After founding and successfully exiting my first company, I'm now scaling my second, a B2B AI SaaS platform for the SME market.

My focus is on creating operational excellence that drives measurable revenue growth.

My Track Record as a GTM Builder:
✓ Founding & Exiting: Built and sold The Scalelab, a B2B outbound agency. Now scaling Scalelist towards $1M ARR.
✓ GTM Architecture: Designed and executed strategies generating over $150M in sales pipeline for high-growth FinTechs & SMEs.
✓ AI-Powered Sales Ops: Implemented AI across the sales stack to optimize everything from forecasting and territory planning to automated prospecting and pipeline reviews.
✓ Team Leadership & Enablement: Recruited, mentored, and led high-performing AE teams to exceed revenue targets. Codified my methods in a sales course used by 1000+ reps globally.
✓ Being recognized as a Forbes 30 under 30 honoree.

I am passionate about leveraging data and AI to solve complex revenue challenges and operate with the high-horsepower, founder-led intensity required to win in today's market.

Specialties: Go-To-Market (GTM) Strategy, Sales Operations, AI Integration, B2B SaaS, FinTech, Founder-Led Sales.

elements.description:
www.thescalelab.com

The Scalelab is a GTM agency helping B2B sales teams hit their sales targets, by generating warm leads for them, week after week, month after month. All through cold call, cold email and LinkedIn.

Companies we help have following 3 problems:
- Rely mostly on inbound to grow which hit a ceiling
- Sales/Marketing teams are stretched too thin
- And have limited outbound experience

They have following 3 goals:
- Generate consistent revenue from outbound
- Reach out to the right people in the right companies at the right time
- Feed their CRM with relevant contacts for future marketing

We come in as a first layer of prospection to help them succeed with outbound using:
- Cold calling
- Cold emailing
- Linkedin lead generation

If this sounds like what you need
=> DM for more info or reach out to youssef@thescalelab.com

elements.description:
Responsible for expanding Nest and Mettā.

1/ Grow Mettā, Nest Management's entrepreneur and startup hub:
- Growth to 1000 members in Hong Kong
- 3x revenue from B2B sales (events, accelerator programs, deal sourcing services and advisory)
- Hosted "Venture Hours" in collaboration with Alibaba's entrepreneur fund (6 sessions, 36 startups, 15 VC investors)
- Managed team of 6 people

Notable personalities taking part in Mettā activities: Vitalik Buterin, Gary Vaynerchuk

2/ Corporate accelerator programs across Asia, Middle East and Africa
- Companies: AIA, DBS Bank, Infinity Motors, Fedex...
- Dealsource series A+ startups to join the programs (32 participating startups in total)
- Operational support throughout the programs
- Investor relations
- Pitch training for investor demo days
- 10 million USD raised by startups

elements.description:
As investor associate I was responsible for:
- Evaluating market trends and generate deal-flow.
- Performing thorough due diligence on some of the most promising startups in the world.
- Acquiring a deep understanding of best investment practices in top tier VCs.
- Expanding personal network to the full range of venture capital investors (from LP to Angels including VC/PE).
- Support fundraising startups by connecting them to the world's leading venture capital investors across all our events.
- 10,000+ individual startup/investor meetings arrange over the course of 2 years and 7 major events.

=> This resulted in startups collectively raising over $1 Billion.

We also organised Venture (venture.websummit.com) the largest gathering of venture capital investors in the world.
